    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-23T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1100 Rogers, James H./20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-23T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 23, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 23—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. For Morgenthau from Rogers. T. V. Soong<note n="15" xml:id="d322fn15">Member
                        of standing committee of Chinese National Economic Council.</note> last week
                    took position United States Government could not undertake alone raising world
                    price silver as too great purchases might be required. Minister of Finance Kung
                    is publicly committed to stability silver price.</p>
                <p>Account demand for stability by important groups already reported believe Nanking
                    Government would welcome some plan assuring future stability silver price in
                    terms of major currencies. [Rogers.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
